# Bot Memory

This file is read on every conversation. Write things here that the bot should
always remember about the user, the brand, and past interactions.

The bot can also update this file during conversations (via the /learn command
or automatic preference summarization).

## User Preferences

- (e.g., "Prefers dark backgrounds for images")
- (e.g., "Likes short punchy captions under 100 chars")
- (e.g., "Hates hashtags — never use them")

## Brand Context

- (e.g., "We just launched our SDK beta on March 3")
- (e.g., "Main competitors are Hyperliquid and dYdX")
- (e.g., "Our Discord launched last week")

## Conversation Notes

- (e.g., "User mentioned they want more meme content this week")
- (e.g., "User prefers to review drafts in the morning")

## Learned Patterns

- (Auto-populated from feedback over time)
